{
  "stem": "20021.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every once in a while, I remember, a brick was thrown at me and I had the-- you know, damaged something there for a while that I had to-- and I ultimately recovered.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I tried not to find myself go walking alone in a non-Jewish neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That would have been dangerous, likely to be attacked and so forth, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- and as time went on, you heard also through the newspapers the Poles were openly advocating that the Jews be expelled from Poland.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not-- it wasn't the government official line, but there were very strong organizations in Poland, which had access to the media, you know, and to the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would announce publicly that Poland has a big problem and the Jews represent that problem and the only solution to that problem is like sending them to Madagascar or something like that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there was an organized boycott of Jewish shops, say like in the '30s, the later '30s.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was official.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Like even in the town of Tarnow was an organized boycott of Jewish shops and so forth.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, my father at one point hired the former major of the army, retired and so forth, to represent him, because he got a big contract from the air force for a base which they were building.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was supplying the chemicals to insulate the roofs and so forth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he hired this major, because he realized that there was this anti-Semitism towards him personally, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was felt in various ways, but it definitely existed there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we didn't have as children or youths growing up, young boys, we hardly had any contact with-- with Polish Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The home was observant, religious, strict kosher service.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
